Use the standard library
This is how to has_close_elements of numbers and threshold:
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this numbers's length times:
      Remember that j is sum of i and 1
      Remember that remaining is diff of numbers's length and j
      Do this remaining times:
         Remember that gap is abs of (diff of item i in numbers and item j in numbers)
         When gap is less than threshold, then:
            The answer is 1
         End when
         Increase j
      End do
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is 0
